knowledge_graph.title: Liverpool F.C.
knowledge_graph.description: Liverpool Football Club is a professional football club based in Liverpool, England. The club competes in the Premier League, the top tier of English football. Founded in 1892, the club joined the Football League the following year and has played its home games at Anfield since its formation.

related_questions.question: What do you call a Liverpool fan?
related_questions.snippet: Liverpool fans often refer to themselves as Kopites, a reference to the fans who once stood, and now sit, on the Kop at Anfield. In 2008 a group of fans decided to form a splinter club, A.F.C. Liverpool, to play matches for fans who had been priced out of watching Premier League football.

related_questions.question: Why do people support Liverpool?
related_questions.snippet: Liverpool has won 18 League titles (second most in English football), seven FA Cups and a record eight League Cups. Also, the Reds have won more European titles than any other English club, with five European Cups, three UEFA Cups and three UEFA Super Cups.

related_questions.question: Is Liverpool FC Catholic or Protestant?
related_questions.snippet: It has been traditionally claimed that Everton FC is 'the Catholic team' of Merseyside, whereas Liverpool FC is 'the Protestant team'. From a historical perspective, the proposition has a potential plausibility.
related_questions.title: Everton and Liverpool Football Clubs: New Gods (Chapter 9)

related_questions.question: Is Liverpool an Irish city?
related_questions.snippet: Liverpool's Irish connections, though, go well beyond football. Today, an estimated 75% percent of Liverpool's population have some Irish ancestry and the city is celebrated for having the strongest Irish heritage of any British city - perhaps besides Glasgow.
related_questions.title: Liverpool is a city with deep Irish roots
